{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"53429ae2-8c86-4ecb-aae0-3e2a8fed7656","content":"Here's the skip attribute for each framework:\n\n**MSTest**\n```csharp\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**xUnit**\n```csharp\n[Fact(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n// or for theories:\n[Theory(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**NUnit**\n```csharp\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**TUnit**\n```csharp\n[Skip(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\nAll four will mark the test as skipped/ignored in test results and display your reason message in the output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"87c6362c-3dc1-4668-aecc-026db387a14a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about the correct attribute syntax for skipping tests with a reason message in each of the four .NET test frameworks: MSTest, xUnit, NUnit, and TUnit. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly without needing to invoke tools.","outputTokens":221,"requestId":"E3C3:229C6C:167FB7E:193C8CB:6A052396"},"id":"e7435599-14de-45db-befd-519d58a400bf","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:21:32.732Z","parentId":"b33e64fc-c7e7-47ae-9791-c5af4d19a7ab"}
